message_1: What is the output of the SHA-256 cryptographic hash function when applied to the message "Hello World"?
message_2:
To compute the SHA-256 hash of the message "Hello World", you can use a programming language or an online tool. Here's the Python code to do it:

```python
import hashlib

message = "Hello World"
hash_object = hashlib.sha256(message.encode())
hash_hex = hash_object.hexdigest()

print(hash_hex)
```

The output of the SHA-256 cryptographic hash function when applied to the message "Hello World" is:
